**Session 37** — external WordPress-Admin-Environment, remote transport, 2026-06-17, 77 calls. The **direct sequel to Session 33**: the agent opened by running `reauthenticate` to switch the remote identity to an **editor** account, then created the WPDS 6.9 design-token variable set — **135 variables created + 83 updated** for a server-side-derived Dark mode, 0 failures — and evaluated re-linking old Button/IconButton instances to WPDS 22.3 `@wordpress/ui` variants.

**What worked well**
- Re-auth-to-editor unblocked everything (practical fix for [BUG-015]; corroborates Session 34).
- Batched variable CRUD with zero failures; clever `/tmp` Node-script dark-mode hex derivation from `@wordpress/theme` color ramps; clean prototype-instance cleanup; AskUserQuestion used only for real design ambiguity.

**Findings (2 new + 3 corroborations)**
