## Summary

**Session 39** (`de1c4083…`) was a **benchmark orchestration** transcript — 168 calls / 35 Figma, 99 min — building the WPDS seed and running two head-to-head rounds (Figmagent vs. official Figma MCP). The actual canvas builds happened in **5 delegated agents whose sub-transcripts weren't captured** (`subAgents: {}`), so this analysis covers the orchestrator's seed-build, verification, and file-reset work.

**Findings:**
- **TOOL-023 (new, P2)** — All 6 `run_script` calls were page CRUD (create/rename/delete page, reset file to pristine seed between contestants). Figmagent has no first-class page management, so every page op falls to the remote-only escape hatch. Proposed `write({type:"PAGE"})` / rename via `edit` / `delete` on PAGE nodes.
- **BUG-016 (existing, P1)** — The `screenshot` `-32602 invalid_union` failed on the 390×844 login frame (`2003:10153`) while mid-size siblings exported fine. This session **confirms it's not agent-specific** — it fired from the orchestrator's own verification path, not just delegated agents. Added session 39 to its affected list with a recurrence note.

**What worked well:** server-side `create_variables` payload generation (37+16 vars + 9 styles in 3 calls), atomic `run_script` file-reset for benchmark hygiene, sub-agent delegation keeping orchestrator context lean, batched screenshot verification (TOOL-017), and in-line diagnosis with no retry storms.

The 2 `Edit` "file not read" errors were generic Claude Code workflow slips, not Figmagent issues — not tracked.

The remaining 4 "needs analysis" sessions in the manifest are mtime-drift false positives (already analyzed; bulk-touched source JSONs), so they don't require re-analysis.
